WorldStage Newsonline– Nigeria’s Federal Fire Service (FFS) said property worth N23 billion was destroyed by fire in the last quarter of 2022 and 28 lives lost in 649 incidences. The service in its statistical information showed that a total of 29 lives were saved with 40 rescued and N145.4billion estimated property saved within the period under review. The statistics also showed that the causes of the fire incidents were due to various reasons, ranging from electrical equipment and high voltage from PHCN. Others are illegal storage of petroleum products, bush fire, electrical spark, among others. It said the affected areas include private dwellings, educational establishment, shops and clubs. Others are hotels, restaurants, factories, banks, petrol stations, transformer, oil/gas, timber sheds, automobiles, markets, plane crash, among others.